Superannuation Contribution Capital Gains Tax Small Business Retirement Exemption Amount
The amount of small business retirement exemption that applies to capital gains
Superannuation Contribution Contributions Excluded By Trustee Amount
The amount of contributions that the trustee of a public sector superannuation scheme, with the contributor's consent, chooses not to include in its assessable income
Superannuation Contribution Employer Contributions Excluding Salary Sacrifice Amount

Employer contributions into superannuation is where an employer provides contributions towards post-employment benefits for one or more employees. Post-employment benefits are employee benefits (other than termination benefits) which are payable after the completion of employment.
Salary sacrifice is an arrangement where an employee agrees to forego part of their pre-tax salary in return for benefits Includes: expenses relating to employer funded defined benefits scheme; and provisions for employer contributions into superannuation.
Employer contributions into superannuation excluding salary sacrifice excludes salary sacrifice earnings paid on behalf of employees to superannuation schemes.
Superannuation Contribution Employer Contributions Salary Sacrificed Amount

Salary sacrificing is a special arrangement between employers and employees where the pre-tax salary of an employee is sacrificed in return for employment related benefits. Salary sacrificing is used by taxpayers who attract income tax at a high marginal tax rate to obtain benefits which instead attract fringe benefit tax at a lower rate, and therefore cost the employee less than if they had used after-tax salary to obtain the same benefit.
Salary sacrificed earnings from superannuation refers to the salary sacrificed earnings paid on behalf of employees.
Superannuation Contribution Employer Contributions Tax File Number Not Quoted Amount
The total amount of all employer contributions received for a member who has not quoted a Tax File Number
Superannuation Contribution Employer Contributions Amount

Employer contributions into superannuation is where an employer provides contributions towards post-employment benefits for one or more employees. It includes salary sacrificed earning paid on behalf of employees to Superannuation schemes.
Superannuation Contribution Family And Friend Contributions Other Amount
Contributions made by other family or friends on behalf of a member.
Superannuation Contribution Foreign Superannuation Fund Assessable Amount
The amount transferred from a foreign superannuation fund or scheme that exceeds the amount that was vested in the member at the time of transfer that is included in the assessable income of the fund
Superannuation Contribution Foreign Superannuation Fund Non Assessable Amount
The amount transferred from a foreign superannuation fund or scheme that is not included in the assessable income of the fund

Superannuation Contribution Personal Injury Election Amount

Enter all personal injury payment amounts that were made under an exemption, and about which the member informed the fund before, or when, the member made the contribution (to ensure its exclusion from the non-concessional contributions cap)
Superannuation Contribution Pooled Super Trusts Contributions Amount

This item is to be completed only by superannuation entities that are Pooled Super Trusts. Record the dollar value of contributions income received and receivable from Pooled Super Trust members for the period to date, including contributions from self-employed members. Do not include 'rollovers received'. Show contributions gross of contributions tax and do not deduct entry fees, deferred entry fees, commissions, management fees or any other ongoing fees or charges deducted from the contributions received (where applicable to the superannuation entity).
Superannuation Contribution Reduced Contributions Amount

Enter the amount that a complying superannuation fund chooses to reduce contributions that would otherwise be included in its assessable income, by applying that amount of available pre-1 July 1988 funding credits.
Superannuation Contribution Spouse And Child Contributions Amount
Contributions made by a spouse or on behalf of a member under 18 years of age
Superannuation Contribution Total Other Amount
This is a balancing item within the list in which it is being used
Superannuation Contribution Total Amount

Total superannuation contributions. Do not include 'rollovers received'. Show contributions gross of contributions tax and do not deduct entry fees, deferred entry fees, commissions, management fees or any other ongoing fees or charges deducted from the contributions received (where applicable to the superannuation entity).
Superannuation Contribution Transfer From Reserve Assessable Amount
The assessable amount transferred to the member's account from a reserve.
Superannuation Contribution Transfer From Reserve Non Assessable Amount
The non-assessable amount transfered to the member's account from a reserve.
Superannuation Fund Details Australian Superannuation Fund Status Indicator

Indication of the status of the superannuation fund - set to True if the superannuation fund qualifies as an Australian Superannuation Fund. The entity is an Australian superannuation fund if it satisfies all three of the following tests at the same time during the income year: the fund is established in Australia, or any asset of the fund is situated in Australia at that time, and at that time, the central management and control of the fund is ordinarily in Australia, and at that time, either the fund had no active member or at least 50% of: the total market value of the fund's assets attributable to superannuation interests held by active members, or the sum of the amounts that would be payable to, or in respect of, active members if they voluntarily ceased to be members is attributable to superannuation interests held by active members who are Australian residents.
An active member is a member covered by subsection 295-95(3) of the ITAA 1997 if the member is either: a contributor to the fund or an individual on whose behalf contributions are made, unless they are a foreign resident for whom the only contributions made to the fund are payments in respect of a time when they were an Australian resident.
The central management and control of a superannuation fund is taken to be ordinarily in Australia even if that central management and control is temporarily outside Australia for a period of not more than two years.

A Accumulation fund D Defined benefit fund U Unfunded defined benefit
The code that best describes the 'benefit structure' of the fund.

If applicable, cancelled the entity's Australian Business Number registration.
Superannuation Payment Benefit Lump Sum Compassionate Grounds Amount
Report the expense for benefits paid to members by the Trustee(s) under the early release provisions relating to compassionate grounds.
Superannuation Payment Benefit Lump Sum Death Amount
Report the expense for benefits that have been paid by the Trustee to the nominated beneficiary/dependent or the deceased member's estate due to the death of a member.
Superannuation Payment Benefit Lump Sum Disability Amount
Report the expense for benefits paid to members resulting from total and permanent disability, and for temporary disability/income protection.
Superannuation Payment Benefit Lump Sum Financial Hardship And Compassionate Grounds Amount
Report the expense for benefits paid to members by the Trustee(s) under the early release provisions relating to severe financial hardship or compassionate grounds.
Superannuation Payment Benefit Lump Sum Financial Hardship Amount
Report the expense for benefits paid to members by the Trustee(s) under the early release provisions relating to grounds of severe financial hardship.
Superannuation Payment Benefit Lump Sum Resignation Amount
Report the expense for benefits paid to members as a result of member resignation from the employer.
Superannuation Payment Benefit Lump Sum Retirement Amount
Report the expense for benefits paid to members as a result of retirement. This does not include amounts paid to Members' accounts with other superannuation entities.
Superannuation Payment Benefit Lump Sum Retrenchment And Redundancies Amount
Report the expense for benefits paid to members as a result of retrenchment or redundancy.
Superannuation Payment Benefit Payments Code

P Superannuation income stream benefit (formerly known as pensions) L Superannuation lump sum benefit T Transition to retirement superannuation income stream benefit C Payment is a combination of superannuation lump sum and superannuation income stream benefits
The code that describes the type of benefit payment. If two or more payment types apply, use the code relating to the largest payment.
Superannuation Payment Benefit Pensions Amount

Report the total value of benefits paid to members in the form of a pension. Includes complying pension, allocated pension and annuity payments. Do not include amounts resulting from the commutation of pension benefits.
Superannuation Payment Benefit Total Amount
Total of all lump sum and pension benefit paid directly to members.; i.e. excluding rollovers.
Superannuation Payment Lump Sum Pooled Super Trusts Amount
This item is to be completed only by superannuation entities that are Pooled Super Trusts. Report the expense for payments to unit holders.
Superannuation Payment Other Amount
This is a balancing item within the list in which it is being used
Superannuation Payment Payments To Contributing Employers And Associates Indicator
Indicates whether the fund or trust made a payment or transferred a benefit that is included in the assessable income of the recipient
Superannuation Payment Repatriation To Employer Sponsor Amount

Where the superannuation entity has repatriated funds to an employer sponsor, report the value of the funds repatriated. Do not include other types of payments to the employer sponsor (for example, administration fees paid to the employer sponsor).
Superannuation Regulatory Information Acquired Assets From Related Parties Amount
The value of any assets (other than exempt assets) acquired from related parties
Superannuation Regulatory Information Acquired Assets From Related Parties Indicator
Indicates whether the entity acquired assets (other than exempt assets) from related parties.
Superannuation Regulatory Information All Investments Arms Length Basis Indicator
Indicates whether the entity made and maintained all investments on an arms length basis.
Superannuation Regulatory Information Assets Appropriately Documented Indicator
Indicates whether all entity assets are appropriately documented as owned by the entity.
Superannuation Regulatory Information Auditor Provide Other Services Indicator
Indicates whether the auditor provided services to the entity as either a tax agent, accountant or financial advisor or administrator.
Superannuation Regulatory Information Borrowed For Purposes Not Permissible Indicator
Indicates whether the entity borrowed for purposes that are not permissible.
Superannuation Regulatory Information Carry On A Business Indicator
Indicates whether the entity carried on a business of selling goods or services.
Superannuation Regulatory Information Disqualified Trustees Or Directors Indicator
Indicates whether any trustees or directors are disqualified persons at the reporting date as defined by Superannuation Industry (Supervision) Act 1993.
Superannuation Regulatory Information In House Assets Exceeding Percentage Of Total Assets Indicator
Indicates whether the entity held in-house assets during the year that exceeded the allowed percentage of total assets
Superannuation Regulatory Information Investment In Related Party Amount
The value of related party investments that the entity held at any time during the reporting period that were not in-house assets
Superannuation Regulatory Information Investment In Related Party Indicator
Indicates whether the entity held an investment in a related party at any time during the reporting period.
Superannuation Regulatory Information Loan Lease Or Invest In Related Parties Amount
The value of in-house assets that the entity held at any time during the reporting period
Superannuation Regulatory Information Loan Lease Or Invest In Related Parties Indicator
Indicates whetherthe entity loaned, leased to or invested in related parties.
Superannuation Regulatory Information Money Prodived To Members Without Conditions Met Indicator
Indicates whether the entity provided money to members without a condition of release being met.
Superannuation Regulatory Information Personal Use Of Assets Before Retirement Indicator
Indicates whether members had the personal use of the entity's assets before retirement.
Superannuation Regulatory Information Provide Financial Assistance To Related Member Indicator
Indicates whether the entity lent money or provided financial assistance to a member or relative of a member of the fund.
Superannuation Regulatory Information Receive In Specie Contributions Amount
The value of all in specie contributions that the entity received during the reporting period on behalf of its members
Superannuation Regulatory Information Receive In Specie Contributions Indicator
Indicates whethere the entity received 'in specie' contributions during the reporting period.
Superannuation Regulatory Information Trustees Receive Remuneration Indicator
Indicates whether the trustees of the fund received any remuneration for their services as a trustee.
Superannuation Rollover Net Amount

Record: * The Net value of member's benefits that have been rolled over/transferred in to the reporting superannuation entity from another superannuation entity ; less * The Net value of member's benefits that have been rolled over/transferred out from the reporting superannuation entity to another superannuation entity
Superannuation Rollover Paid Amount
Superannuation Rollover Received Amount

Record the gross value of member's benefits that have been rolled over/transferred in to the reporting superannuation entity from another superannuation entity. Include amounts received on behalf of both new and existing members. Include rollovers/transfers between superannuation entities where a single employer sponsors several superannuation entities, but not between sub-plans of a single master trust. Do not include amounts that are new to the superannuation system (i.e. do not include amounts that have not been received by a previous superannuation entity).
